1 Section 24A.16. A. Except as set forth in subsection B of this
2 section, public educational institutions and their employees may
3 keep confidential:
4 1. Individual student records;
5 2. Teacher lesson plans, tests and other teaching material;
6 3. Personal communications concerning individual students; and
7 4. Any contract for use of a student athlete’s name, image, or
8 likeness disclosed to a postsecondary institution pursuant to the
9 Student Athlete Name, Image and Likeness Rights Act.
10 B. If kept, statistical information not identified with a
11 particular student and directory information shall be open for
12 inspection and copying. Except as provided in subsection C of this
13 section, each educational institution may choose to designate
14 specific information which shall be classified as directory
15 information for students attending the educational institution. In
16 accordance with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act,
17 Section 1232g of Title 20 of the United States Code and Part 99 of
18 Title 34 of the Code of Federal Regulations, “directory information”
19 includes a student’s name, address, telephone listing, date and
20 place of birth, major field of study, participation in officially
21 recognized activities and sports, weight and height of members of
22 athletic teams, dates of attendance, degrees and awards received,
23 and the most recent previous educational institution attended by the
24 student. Any educational agency or institution making public
