1 dire ctory information shall give public notice of the categories of
2 information which it has designated as directory information with
3 respect to each student attending the institution or agency and
4 shall allow a reasonable period of time after the notice has been
5 given for a parent or guardian to inform the institution or agency
6 that any or all of the information designated should not be released
7 without prior consent of the parent or guardian or the student if
8 the student is eighteen (18) years of age or older.
9 C. All educational agencies or institutions which are not the
10 primary custodians of student directory information of students
11 attending the educational institution, but which are allowed to
12 access the information for educational purposes, shall be prohibited
13 from releasing or selling any or all student directory information
14 unless disclosure is authorized by the Family Educational Rights and
15 Privacy Act, Section 1232g of Title 20 of the United States Code and
16 Part 99 of Title 34 of the Code of Federal Regulations, or Section
17 3-168 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
18 D. A public school district may release individual student
19 records for the current or previous school year to a school district
20 at which the student was previously enrolled for purposes of
21 evaluating educational programs and school effectiveness.
22 E. Notwithstanding any provisions of this section, public
23 educational institutions and their employees shall release all
24 requested student records to the student's parent or guardian, or to
