1 the student themselves if he or she is eighteen (18) years of age or
2 older, if the records are requested by the parent, guardian, or the
3 adult student. Such records shall be provided in a timely manner in
4 accordance with the Oklahoma Open Records Act. An educational
5 institution shall provide such records free of charge, and shall not
6 redact or otherwise omit any information from the record, unless
7 including such information would violate the law. Records related
8 to a student include, but are not limited to, personal
9 communications concerning the student related to IEPs, behaviors
10 that result in a disciplinary action, or official school activities
11 including student-teacher meetings, any school staff or teacher
12 correspondence, individual student records, meeting notes, student
13 athlete contracts, proposed changes to an Individualized Education
14 Program or other program for students with disabilities, student
15 assessments, progress reports, and internal complaints and
16 recommendations regarding the student.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
